#Approach:

💡 IDEA
- Har step par current first non-repeating character chahiye.
- Queue potential answers maintain karegi.
- Frequency array batayegi character kitni baar aaya hai.
- Queue ke front par hamesha first non-repeating character rakhne ki koshish karenge.

⚙️ APPROACH
1. Character stream ko ek-ek karke process karo.
2. Character ko queue me daalo.
3. Uski frequency increase karo.
4. Jab tak queue ka front repeating hai (freq > 1):
   - Queue se remove kar do.
5. Agar queue empty ho gayi:
   - '#' append karo.
6. Otherwise:
   - Queue ka front append karo.

📝 EXAMPLE

Input = "abac"

Step 1:
a

freq[a]=1
Queue = [a]

Answer = a

----------------

Step 2:
b

freq[b]=1
Queue = [a,b]

Answer = a

----------------

Step 3:
a

freq[a]=2
Queue = [a,b,a]

Front a repeating hai
remove a

Queue = [b,a]

Answer = b

----------------

Step 4:
c

freq[c]=1
Queue = [b,a,c]

Front b non-repeating hai

Answer = b

Final = "aabb"

❓ WHY QUEUE + FREQ ARRAY

Queue:
- Arrival order maintain karti hai.
- First non-repeating candidate front par milta hai.

Frequency Array:
- O(1) me pata chal jata hai repeating hai ya nahi.

Dono combine karke first valid character instantly mil jata hai.

⏱️ COMPLEXITY
Time  : O(N)

Reason:
- Har character queue me ek baar enter hota hai.
- Har character maximum ek baar remove hota hai.

Space : O(N)
         (Queue)

         + O(26)
         (Frequency Array)

🎯 INTERVIEW POINT
- Queue me repeating characters reh sakte hain.
- Isliye while loop mandatory hai.
- Queue front ko repeatedly remove karo jab tak non-repeating na mil jaye.
- Queue = order maintain
- Freq Array = repetition check
- Stream problems me Queue + Frequency bahut common pattern hai.

#Code:

import java.util.*; 

public class Solution {

	public static String FirstNonRepeating(String A)
	{
		//You can code here
    StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
    Queue<Character> q = new LinkedList<>();
    int[] freq = new int[26];

    for(int i=0; i<A.length(); i++){
      char c = A.charAt(i);

      q.offer(c);
      freq[c - 'a']++;

      while(!q.isEmpty() && freq[q.peek() - 'a'] > 1){
        q.poll();
      }

      if(q.isEmpty()){
        sb.append('#');
      }
      else{
        sb.append(q.peek());
      }
    }
    return sb.toString();
	}
}
